# Discharge Baseline Computation — Implementation Plan

Compute long-term mean river discharge for all 40 hydro-stations using 5 years (2020–2024) of GloFAS historical data. Derive flood thresholds using fixed multipliers of the mean.

## Threshold Logic

| Risk Level | Condition | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| **Safe** | forecast < 2× mean | Normal or slightly elevated flow |
| **Alert** | forecast ≥ 2× mean | Notably above normal |
| **Minor Flood** | forecast ≥ 5× mean | Significantly above normal |
| **Major Flood** | forecast ≥ 10× mean | Extreme flow |

## How It Works

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A["tools/discharge_baselines/compute.php"] --> B["Fetch 40 stations\nfrom ArcGIS"]
    B --> C["For each station:\nquery Open-Meteo\n2020-01-01 to 2024-12-31"]
    C --> D["Compute mean\nfrom ~1827 daily values"]
    D --> E["Derive thresholds:\nalert = 2× mean\nminor = 5× mean\nmajor = 10× mean"]
    E --> F["Write constants:\nmodules/forecast/\ndischarge_thresholds.php"]
```

